{"lemma":"فَرِيضَةٌ","slug":"فَرِيضَةٌ","root":"ف.ر.ض","root_slug":"ف-ر-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَرِيضَة","root":"فرض","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33580"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B6%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"duty, obligation, assignment"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun from the verb فَرَضَ (faraḍa)."},"ipa":["/fa.riː.dˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33580","headword_ar":"فَرِيضَةٌ","root":"frD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylapN","text_ar":"فَعِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlapN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iDu","text_ar":"فَرَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": said by some to be derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroDN","text_ar":"فَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the act of “ apportioning, ” or “ appointing; ” because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frAy^D","text_ar":"فرايض"},{"kind":"text","text":"are apportioned, or appointed: by others said to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroDN","text_ar":"فَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to a bow. (Msb.) [These remarks apply to the word in all the senses here following.] ―         -b2-  A subst. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing made obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding, on a person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obligatory statute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ordinance of God, in a general sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share, made obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,) on a man: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything apportioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a primarily-apportioned inheritance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see an ex. in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewl","text_ar":"عول"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] and hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iDu","text_ar":"فَرَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shares, of inheritances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed primary portions of inheritances assigned by the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Kur-án;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which are a half, third, fourth, sixth, and eighth;] because they are apportioned, or appointed, to their several owners. (Mgh.) And hence, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu AlfaraAy^iDi","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الفَرَايِضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and elliptically"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaraAy^iDu","text_ar":"الفَرَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * Mgh, O, * Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The science of the division of inheritances;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the science of questions relating to inheritance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) It is said in a trad., (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEal~amuwA AlfaraAy^iDa waEal~imuwhaA","text_ar":"تَعَلَّمُوا الفَرَايِضَ وَعَلِّمُوهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsa faA_in~ahaA niSofu AlEilomi","text_ar":"النَّاسَ فَاـِنَّهَا نِصْفُ العِلْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the relation commonly followed, with the pron. fem., referring to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfrAy^D","text_ar":"الفرايض"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEal~imuwhu faA_in~ahu","text_ar":"وَعَلِّمُوهُ فَاـِنَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the pron. masc., referring to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilom","text_ar":"عِلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"understood as prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfrAy^D","text_ar":"الفرايض"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Learn ye the science of the division of inheritances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and teach ye it to"},{"kind":"text","text":"(other)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men, for it is the half of science:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] it is said to be called the half of science in consideration of the division of statutes into those which pertain to the living and those which pertain to the dead; or by way of amplification. (Mgh, * Msb.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfariyDapu","text_ar":"الفَرِيضَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAdilapu","text_ar":"العَادِلَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The equitable portion of inheritance"},{"kind":"text","text":"], in a trad. of Ibn-'Omár, is that respecting which the Muslims have agreed: or that for which the authority is elicited from the Kur-án and the Sunneh without there being in these any express statute respecting it: or that is equitably divided, agreeably with the portions and shares mentioned in the Kur-án and the Sunneh. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is made obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the owner, to give,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of pasturing beasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in payment of the poor-rate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel that is taken in payment of the poor-rate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so termed because it is made obligatory to be given, of a certain number of camels: the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added because the word is made a subst., not an epithet: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iDu","text_ar":"فَرَايِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAy^iDu AlA_ibili","text_ar":"فَرَايِضُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dues of the poor-rate, of camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh: *) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fryDp","text_ar":"فريضة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of twenty-five camels is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binot maxaAD","text_ar":"بِنْت مَخَاض"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or she-camel one year old; (AHeyth;) that of thirty-six, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binot","text_ar":"بِنْت"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuwn","text_ar":"لَبُون"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, Mgh,) or she-camel two years old; (AHeyth;) that of forty-six, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiq~ap","text_ar":"حِقَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or she-camel three years old; and that of sixty-one, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*aEap","text_ar":"جَذَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or she-camel four years old. (AHeyth.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfariyDataAni","text_ar":"الفَرِيضَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*aEap","text_ar":"جَذَعَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hiq~ap","text_ar":"حِقَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuroDataAni","text_ar":"الفُرْضَتَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same, accord. to ISk. (IB.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyDapN","text_ar":"فَرِيضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by an extension of its meaning, is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in other cases than those of the poor-rate. (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAriDN","text_ar":"فَارِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","TA","AHeyth"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%81%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%B6%D8%A9/","headword_ar":"فريضة","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23466#43320c","body_html":"<span>الفريضة: فعيلة من الفرض وهو في اللغة التقدير، وفي الشرع: ما ثبت بدليل مقطوع كالكتاب والسنة والإجماع، وهو على نوعين: فرض عين، وفرض كفاية، ففرض العين: ما يلزم كل واحد إقامته ولا يسقط عن البعض بإقامة البعض، كالإيمان ونحوه، وفرض الكفاية: ما يلزم جميع المسلمين إقامته ويسقط بإقامة البعض عن الباقين كالجهاد وصلاة الجنازة. </span>"}]}}